%S A061607 1,140,4590,72856,736270,5437530,31812872,155306560,655619994,
%T A061607 2455575200,8318383084,25866206928,74695843040,202207425140,
%U A061607 517078904040,1256977290880,2920224416195,6512959507500,13998652002570,29092569815400,58629910765230,114866641798590
%N A061607 Ooguri-Vafa invariants of disk domain wall degeneracies for brane I in the O(K) -> P^1 X P^1 geometry.
%C A061607 This is row k[s] = 5 in Table 1, "m = 1", of the Aganagic-Klemm-Vafa paper (page 20) and preprint (page 38). Due to the formula (6.9), also the opposite of row k[s] = 5 in Table 2, "m = -1", up to the offset/leading 0. - _M. F. Hasler_, Nov 03 2025
%C A061607 See A061606 for further details. - _Steven Kotlarz_, Apr 09 2026
%H A061607 Steven Kotlarz, <a href="/A061607/b061607.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..200</a>
%H A061607 Mina Aganagic, Albrecht Klemm, and Cumrun Vafa, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1515/zna-2002-1-201">Disk Instantons, Mirror Symmetry and the Duality Web</a>, Z. Naturforsch. A 57 (2002), 1-28; also <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/0105045">arXiv:hep-th/0105045</a>, 2001.
%F A061607 a(n) = (n+1) * Sum_{k=0..6} h(k) * binomial(n-k+16, 16), where h = (1, 53, 476, 1044, 476, 53, 1). - _Steven Kotlarz_, Apr 09 2026
%o A061607 (Python)
%o A061607 from math import comb
%o A061607 def a(n):
%o A061607     h = [1, 53, 476, 1044, 476, 53, 1]
%o A061607     return (n+1) * sum(h[k] * comb(n-k+16, 16) for k in range(7))
%o A061607 print([a(n) for n in range(22)]) # _Steven Kotlarz_, Apr 09 2026
%o A061607 (PARI) a(n) = {my(h=[1,53,476,1044,476,53,1]); (n+1)*sum(k=0,6,h[k+1]*binomial(n-k+16,16))} \\ _Steven Kotlarz_, Apr 09 2026
